author: The Current
description:
Nanna and Ragnar from Of Monsters and Men talk about the Icelandic influence
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

During an interview with Gannon in The Current studio, Of Monsters and Men speculate on how the Icelandic landscape finds its way into their music. 

Of Monsters and Men’s 2025 album, "All Is Love and Pain in the Mouse Parade," is available on Skarkali Records/Virgin Music Group.

Musicians
Nanna Bryndis Hilmarsdottir - vocals, guitar
Ragnar Thorhallsson - vocals, guitar, piano
Brynjar Leifsson - guitar, vocals
Kristjan Kristjansson - bass, vocals
Arnar Hilmarsson - drums

Texas singer-songwriter Hayes Carll released his 10th album, "We’re Only Human," on August 8. While on tour in support of the album, Carll visited The Current to play songs from the new record and to catch up with host Bill DeVille. 

Watch and listen to a performance of "High" above.
